  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "Recommended update for libXfont",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "\nThis update for libXfont fixes the following issues:\n\n- The original fix for CVE-2015-1804 prevented DWIDTH to be negative. However, the\n  spec states that 'DWIDTH [...] is a vector indicating the position of the next\n  glyph's origin relative to the origin of this glyph'. Consequently, negative\n  DWIDTH values should be allowed. (bsc#958383)\n",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
